S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Administrative Division
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A generic term for an administrative region within a country at a level below that of the sovereign state.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Agency Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of an agency, entity or organization.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Agency Responsible for Production
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifies the agency which produced the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Application Profile
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of an application profile that can be used with the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Approximate Grid Resolution
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Approximate grid resolution for nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Catalogue Element Classification
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a catalogue element.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ENC
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electronic Navigational Chart

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bathymetric Chart
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A topographic chart of the bed of a body of water, or a part of it. Generally, bathymetric charts show depths by contour lines and gradient tints.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water Level Product
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Water Level Information for Surface Navigation

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Surface Current Product
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A product representing the water velocity at one or more geographic locations down to a given depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: MSI Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An outage of a maritime safety information broadcast service (satellite or terrestrial system).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AtoN Information
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing information related to Marine Aids to Navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Catalogue Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing structured records of items.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Routeing Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Services associated with Ships Routeing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Information
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Newly discovered icebergs, changes to ice conditions and ice related information likely to impact navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Routeing Information
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information associated with Ships Routeing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Purpose Chart
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any chart designed primarily to meet specific requirements.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautical Publication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A (nautical chart or) nautical publication is a "a special-purpose map or book, or a specially compiled database from which such a map or book is derived, that is issued officially by or on the authority of a Government, authorized Hydrographic Office or other relevant government institution and is designed to meet the requirements of marine navigation".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Printed Nautical Chart
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A printed nautical chart is a "a special-purpose map , that is issued officially by or on the authority of a Government, authorized Hydrographic Office or other relevant government institution and is designed to meet the requirements of marine navigation".

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Catalogue Element Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier of a catalogue element.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Catalogue Section Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A number identifying a section within a catalogue.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Catalogue Section Title
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The catalogue section title.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Authority
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of person, government agency or organisation granted powers of managing or controlling access to and/or activity in an area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The administration to prevent or detect and prosecute violations of rules and regulations at international boundaries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The department of government, or civil force, charged with maintaining public order.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Person or corporation, owners of, or entrusted with or invested with the power of managing a port. May be called a Harbour Board, Port Trust, Port Commission, Harbour Commission, Marine Department.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Immigration
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority controlling people entering a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for checking the validity of the health declaration of a vessel and for declaring free pratique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coast Guard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Organization keeping watch on shipping and coastal waters according to governmental law; normally the authority with responsibility for search and rescue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Agricultural
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for preventing infection of the agriculture of a country and for the protection of the agricultural interests of a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A military authority which provides control of access to or approval for transit through designated areas or airspace.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private Company
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A private or publicly owned company or commercial enterprise which exercises control of facilities, for example a calibration area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime Police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A governmental or military force with jurisdiction in territorial waters. Examples could include Gendarmerie Maritime, Carabinierie, and Guardia Civil.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Environmental
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the protection of the environment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control of fisheries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Finance
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control and movement of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A national or regional authority charged with administration of maritime affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The agency or establishment for collecting duties, tolls.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hydrographic Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: State agency in charge of marine surveys and hydrography.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RENC
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Regional ENC Coordination Centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: VARs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Value Added Resellers (VARs), who are able to offer comprehensive end-use services that bring together various navigational products into one package.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Character Encoding
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Designation of the character set to be used to encode the textual value of the locale.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: City Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a town or city.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Classification
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates a classification.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Comment
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Comment regarding an entity obvious from context.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Compilation Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: In ECDIS, the scale at which the data was compiled.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Compression Flag
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates if the resource is compressed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Instructions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Contract Period
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Definition of a period when a contract is valid.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Country Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Currency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Something (such as coins, treasury notes, and banknotes) that is in circulation as a medium of exchange.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Dataset Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name or identification of a dataset.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Delivery Point
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Details of where post can be delivered such as the apartment, name and/or number of a street, building or PO Box.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Digital Signature Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Value derived from the digital signature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ID
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meta data record identifier for QualityOfBathymetric Coverage

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Digital Signature Reference
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Specifies the algorithm used to compute digital signature value.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name Usage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the type and display level of the name of a feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Default Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to the default name/text display setting.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternate Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to an alternate name/text display setting, for example an alternate language.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Chart Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name or text is not intended to be displayed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distribution Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Supply status of nautical products.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Production
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A product or service that is currently in production.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Withdrawn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A product or service that has been withdrawn.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Distributor Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the distributor.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Domestic Carriage Requirements
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A carriage requirement that is specific to a country or region and is based on domestic legislation or regulation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date of publishing for example of a publication, chart, or product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Edition of the ENC being referenced.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Expiration Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expiration date of a product or service

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a file within a system.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: IMO Maritime Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A maritime service as identified by the International Maritime Organization (IMO).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vessel Traffic Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any service implemented by a relevant authority primarily designed to improve safety and efficiency of traffic flow and the protection of the environment. It may range from simple information messages, to extensive organization of the traffic involving national or regional schemes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aids to Navigation Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing up-to-date information of Aids to Navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved for Future Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An option that is reserved for future use

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Support Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service that provides information necessary to organize and support port calls and varies depending on the local needs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime Safety Information Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing navigational and meteorological warnings, meteorological forecasts and other urgent safety-related messages broadcast to ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilotage Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The services of a person who directs the movements of a vessel through pilot waters, usually a person who has demonstrated extensive knowledge of channels, aids to navigation, dangers to navigation, etc., in a particular area and is licensed for that area, are available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tug Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service that contributes to the safety of navigation, protection of the marine environment, and efficiency of marine transportation by conducting different types of operations including tugboats, such as ship assistance, salvalge, towage, escort etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vessel Shore Reporting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing information related to Vessel Shore Reporting and Ship reporting systems.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telemedical Assistance Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service to provide decision support and advice to the seafarer on board responsible for medical care.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime Assistance Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service to manage communications between the coastal State, ships' officers requiring assistance and other responsible maritime organizations: fleet owners, salvage companies, port authorities, brokers, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautical Chart Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service that provides geospatial information (in digital and / or printed format) to support safe maritime navigation with the aim to fulfill SOLAS regulation V/19.2.1.4 requirements for ships to carry "nautical charts and nautical publications to plan and display the ship's route for the intended voyage and to plot and monitor positions throughout the voyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautical Publications Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service to provide information as a support to the navigation process. This comprises information to complement nautical charts, such as information on ports and sea areas, as well as the contact information of authorities and services for a sea area or port. It further describes regulations, restrictions, recommendations and other nautical information applicable in these areas, and aim to fulfill SOLAS regulation V/19.2.1.4 requirements for ships to carry "nautical charts and nautical publications to plan and display the ship's route for the intended voyage and to plot and monitor positions throughout the voyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Navigation Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service to provide ice navigation information to ships in and in the vicinity of possible ice infested regions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Meteorological Information Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service to provide meteorological information (digitally) to ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Real-Time Hydrographic and Environmental Information Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service providing hydrographic and environmental observations and forecasts, such as water level and surface current information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Search and Rescue Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A service aimed at providing information about and assist with Search and Rescue functions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: International Carriage Requirements
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International Carriage requirements are carriage requirements based on the SOLAS-convention or similar international regulation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ISBN
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International Standard Book Number.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ISO 216
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: ISO 216 is a paper-size standard established by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A0
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The paper size A0, as defined in ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The first size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The paper size A2, as defined in ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A3
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fourth size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A4
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fifth size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A5
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The sixth size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A6
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The seventh size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A7
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The eighth size as output size on nautical paper chart. Referring to ISO 216.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ISSN
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International Standard Serial Number.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Issue Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date up to which the data was made available by the Data Producer.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Issue Time
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Time of day at which the data was made available by the Data Producer.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for online access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Product Mapping
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A classification of the internal relationships between products and services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher Priority Alternative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A higher prioritized or recommended alternative product or service, that can fully replace another.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Priority Alternative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A lower prioritized or not recommended alternative product or service, that can fully replace another.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended Enhancement Provider
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A recommended additional product or service, that provides added value to another.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended Enhancement User
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A product or service, that is recommended to make use of added value provided by another product or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value considered by the Data Producer to be the maximum (largest) scale at which the data is to be displayed before it can be considered to be “grossly overscaled”.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name of Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Not For Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates the dataset is not intended to be used for navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Online Description
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Description of online resources.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Optimum Display Scale

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Original Product Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The original identification of a product that has been re-branded or distributed under multiple identification schemes.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Other Data Type Description

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Postal Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Known in various countries as a postcode, or ZIP code, the postal code is a series of letters and/or digits that identifies each postal delivery area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Price
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The amount of money expected, required, or given in payment for something.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Print Agency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the publishing institution of the paper chart for navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Print Nation

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Producer Nation

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product Number

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product Reference

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Protocol

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Protocol Request
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Request used to access the resource. Structure and content depend on the protocol and standard used by the online resource, such as Web Feature Service standard.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Publication Number

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reprint Edition

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reprint Nation

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reported Date

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm (ECDSA) that uses signatures based on the issuing certificate and generated using the issuer’s P-384 elliptic curve key.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Navigation Purpose

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: TIFF
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Tagged Image File Format (TIFF).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: PDF/A Or U/A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Portable Document Format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: LUA
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lua programming language.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Being the one or ones distinct from that or those first mentioned or implied.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File Purpose
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reason for inclusion of the support file.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: New
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A file which is new.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Replacement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A file which replaces an existing file.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Deletion
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Deletes an existing file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Types of status of services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Provisional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates a temporary, preliminary, or interim status. A provisional item is not yet finalized or fully approved.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Released
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates a finalized, officially approved, or publicly available status. A released item is ready for general use or distribution.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Deprecated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that a feature, method, product, or component is no longer recommended for use but is still available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Deleted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that a feature, method, product, or component is no longer available or has been permanently removed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The production date of the source; for example the date of measurement.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type of the source.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Law or Regulation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Treaty, convention, or international agreement; law or regulation issued by a national or other authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Official Publication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Publication not having the force of law, issued by an international organisation or a national or local administration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mariner Report, Confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reported by mariner(s) and confirmed by another source.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mariner Report, Not Confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reported by mariner(s) but not confirmed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Industry Publications and Reports
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shipping and other industry publications, including graphics, charts and web sites.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Remotely Sensed Images
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from satellite images.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Photographs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Products Issued by HO Services
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from products issued by Hydrographic Offices.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: News Media
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from news media.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Traffic Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Information obtained from the analysis of traffic data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A national or regional authority charged with administration of maritime affairs.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Specific Usage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The use for which the dataset is intended.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose Overview
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: For use in the study of the characteristics of maritime zones, in the formulation of plans, in the selection of routes, etc., showing only relevant elements of the coastline, harbours, islands, principal navigational marks and obstructions, and submarine landforms.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose General
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A nautical chart with universality (i.e., generality) in use, characterized by the requirement that the chart must comprehensively describe various natural elements and socioeconomic elements, and that each element of the subject matter expressed is universal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose Coastal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used for marine navigation, mainly displaying submarine landforms, navigational marks, navigational obstacles and other elements related to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose Approach
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used for near-shore navigation, mainly showing the marine elements close to coastal areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose Harbour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used for entering and leaving harbours, selecting anchorage, studying harbour topography, and carrying out the construction of harbours.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Purpose Berthing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: For ships berthing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An identifier, such as words, numbers, letters, symbols, or any combination of those used to establish a contact to a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of methods of communication over a distance by electrical, electronic, or electromagnetic means.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Voice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The transfer or exchange of information by using sounds that are being made by mouth and throat when speaking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Facsimile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of transmitting and reproducing graphic matter (as printing or still pictures) by means of signals sent over telephone lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SMS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Short Message Service is a form of text messaging communication on phones and mobile phones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of facts, concepts or instructions in a formalised manner suitable for communication, interpretation or processing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Streamed Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is constantly received by and presented to an end-user while being delivered by a provider.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telex
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of communication in which messages are sent over long distances by using a telephone system and are printed by using a special machine (called a teletypewriter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An apparatus, system or process for communication at a distance by electric transmission over wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Email
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Messages and other data exchanged between individuals using computers in a network.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type Of Physical Product
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of a physical (navigational) product, usually printed on paper.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type Of Product Format
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of product format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Geography Markup Language. An XML-based geographic information encoding language developed by the Open GIS Consortium (OGC) to enhance the interoperability of geographic information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ISO/IEC 8211
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Specification for a data descriptive file for information interchange.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: PDF
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Portable Document Format. A file format developed by Adobe in 1993 to present documents, including text formatting and images, in a manner independent of application software, hardware, and operating systems.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: HTML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hypertext Markup Language.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ePub
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: E-book file format.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Paper
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: For printing hydrographic charts, heavyweight, single layer paper is used. Such paper is generally made wholly or partly from rags and simulates hand-made paper. It is strong, moisture resistant and manufactured to withstand surface erasure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: HDF-5
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hierarchical Data Format version 5 is a file format and data model designed for storing and organizing large amounts of numerical data efficiently.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: BSB
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A file format used primarily for storing nautical charts in raster form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GeoTiff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Extension of the TIFF specification to allow the storage of geo- referencing information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Application
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Provision of data in a format including operational functionality, such as a software program designed to perform specific tasks or functions for the user.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: XML
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Extensible Markup Language.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: PNG
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Portable Network Graphics format.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type Of Time Interval Unit
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The unit of a value indicating a time Time Interval.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit of time equal to 60 minutes or 3600 seconds.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Day
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (1) The duration of one rotation of the earth, or occasionally another celestial body, on its axis. It is measured by successive transits of a reference point on the celestial sphere over the meridian, and each type takes its name from the reference used. (2) The period of daylight, as distinguished from night.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Month
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A measure of time based on the motion of the moon in its orbit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Year
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A period of one revolution of the earth around the sun.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Update Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A date referring to the day a product or service was updated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Update Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Update number of the ENC being referenced.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value Of Time
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length or duration of a time interval, referred to a specified time interval unit.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Version
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identification of a specific form or variation of an entity.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Paper Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length in cm of the shorter side of a paper.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Paper Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length in cm of the longer side of a paper.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Publication Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official publication date of a notice, product or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Week Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A consecutive number that specifies a week within a year.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Year Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A number indicating a year.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Datum EPSG Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Horizontal reference as an EPSG code representing a valid entry in the EPSG Geodetic Parameter Dataset, as maintained by the Geodesy Subcommittee of the IOGP Geomatics Committee, and provided online at epsg.org.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: EPSG3395 (World Mercator)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A global Mercator projection commonly used for mapping applications requiring accurate distance measurements near the equator.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: EPSG3857 (Pseudo-Mercator)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A popular web mapping projection used by Google Maps, OpenStreetMap, and Bing Maps. Distorts at the poles but is widely used in online maps.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: EPSG4326 (WGS84)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: World Geodetic System 1984, used globally for GPS and geographic coordinates. Specifies coordinates in latitude and longitude degrees.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the low waters of spring tides. This level is used as a tidal datum in some areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or somewhat lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water Springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides. It was first used in waters surrounding India.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian Spring Low Water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Lower Low Water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equinoctial Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Père, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Low Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Highest High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Low Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Low water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: High water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Mean Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Mean water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equivalent Height of Water (German GlW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low water level which is the result of a defined low water discharge - called "equivalent discharge".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water (German HSW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Upper limit of water levels where navigation is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reference Low Water Level According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 94 % of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 1% of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch River Low Water Reference Level (OLR)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 95% of the year within a period of 20 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Project Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Conditional low water level with established probability.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Normal Backwater Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Highest water level derived from the upper backwater stream in watercourse or reservoir under the normal operational conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ohio River Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Ohio River datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch High Water Reference Level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 2020
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The 2020 update to the International Great Lakes Datum, the official reference system used to measure water level heights in the Great Lakes, connecting channels, and the St. Lawrence River system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Floor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The bottom of the ocean and seas where there is a generally smooth gentle gradient. Also referred to as sea bed (sometimes seabed or sea-bed), and sea bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Surface
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A two-dimensional (in the horizontal plane) field representing the air-sea interface, with high-frequency fluctuations such as wind waves and swell, but not astronomical tides, filtered out.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hydrographic Zero
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference near the lowest astronomical tide (LAT), below which the sea level falls only very exceptionally.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Address
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction or superscription of a letter, package, etc., specifying the name of the place to which it is directed, and optionally a contact person or organisation who should receive it.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Custom Paper Size
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: User specified paper size width x, height y

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Default Locale
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Locale of an option that is selected automatically unless an alternative is specified.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Issuance Cycle
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The cycle of issuing a product or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Online Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about online sources from which a resource or data can be obtained.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The active period of a recurring event or occurrence.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Pricing
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A decision or establishment of a price.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Print Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information on the printing of nautical paper charts.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Print Size
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Size of nautical paper charts.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Product Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of the product specification to which a nautical product adheres.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information on additional files used in addition to nautical products.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Support File Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of the product specification to which a support file adheres.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Service Specification
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of the (product) specification to which a nautical service adheres.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Indication
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about the source document, publication, or reference from which object data or textual material included or referenced in a dataset are derived.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunications
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A means or channel of communicating at a distance by electrical or electromagnetic means such as telegraphy, telephony, or broadcasting.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Interval Of Product
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The temporal interval over which the product is updated or renewed.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Time Interval Of Cycle
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The temporal interval of the cycle over which data is produced.
